## Metadata Requirements

All pages in the `app/` directory **MUST** export a `metadata` object, except for:
- `app/profile` - User profile page (excluded)
- `app/sso-callback` - SSO callback page (excluded)

### Required Metadata Fields

All page metadata objects must include all fields from `lib/seo-config.js`. The metadata structure should follow this pattern:

#### TDK Character Limits

**CRITICAL**: All TDK (Title, Description, Keywords) fields must comply with character limits:

- **Title (T)**: ≤ 60 characters
- **Description (D)**: ≤ 160 characters  
- **Keywords (K)**: < 100 characters (total length of all keywords combined, separated by commas)

```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: string,                    // Page title (≤ 60 characters)
  description: string,              // Page description (≤ 160 characters)
  keywords: string[],               // SEO keywords array (total < 100 characters)
  robots: {
    index: boolean,
    follow: boolean,
    googleBot: {
      index: boolean,
      follow: boolean,
      'max-video-preview': number,
      'max-image-preview': string,
      'max-snippet': number,
    },
  },
  alternates: {
    canonical: string,              // Canonical URL
  },
  openGraph: {
    title: string,
    description: string,
    url: string,
    siteName: string,
    images: Array<{
      url: string,
      width: number,
      height: number,
      alt: string,
    }>,
    locale: string,
    type: string,
  },
  twitter: {
    card: string,
    site: string,
    title: string,
    description: string,
    images: string[],
  },
};
```

### Validation Checklist

When creating or updating pages in `app/`, ensure:
- ✅ `metadata` is exported (except profile and sso-callback pages)
- ✅ All required fields from `lib/seo-config.js` are present
- ✅ **Title length ≤ 60 characters** (check: `metadata.title.length <= 60`)
- ✅ **Description length ≤ 160 characters** (check: `metadata.description.length <= 160`)
- ✅ **Keywords total length < 100 characters** (check: `metadata.keywords.join(', ').length < 100`)
- ✅ Values are appropriate for the specific page
- ✅ URLs use the correct site URL (can use `siteUrl` from `lib/seo-config.js`)
